This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on October 9, 2020, in honor of Columbus Day. The proclamation highlights the historical significance of Christopher Columbus's voyage to the New World and his contributions to American history. It also acknowledges the efforts of Italian Americans in preserving their heritage and emphasizes the need to protect monuments and statues from destruction or vandalism. The proclamation mentions executive orders signed by President Trump to promote patriotic education and preserve the nation's history. The article concludes with the official proclamation of October 12, 2020, as Columbus Day and calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.